---

<ContentPage title="Technology">
	<p class="text-lg font-semibold">
		Technology is the cornerstone of Bethink's operations, propelling innovation and
		shaping the future of e-learning. At the heart of our technological prowess is the
		creation of Klasa, a custom platform that started as a solution for a single course and
		has evolved into a multi-tenant application, navigating numerous scaling challenges
		along its transformative journey.
	</p>

	<h2>Atomic Content</h2>

	<p>
		A pivotal aspect of our technological approach is the implementation of Atomic Content.
		This innovative strategy allows us to seamlessly reuse content across various contexts,
		creating interconnected links that compose diverse and engaging learning experiences.
	</p>

	<p>
		More than just content reuse, it provides students with a contextual space for asking
		questions precisely where they arise, fostering a dynamic and interactive educational
		environment. Additionally, the Atomic Content approach unlocks unique analytical
		capabilities that enrich the learning process, offering insights that go beyond
		traditional learning models.
	</p>

	<ContentPageImage
		src="https://res.cloudinary.com/bethink/image/upload/v1700505540/bethinkgroup__hero.png"
		caption="Atomic content approach enables content composition and contextual communication"
		classes="max-w-[500px] mx-auto"
	/>

	<h2>Unique Challenges</h2>

	<p>
		Bethink's tech department excels in navigating unique challenges inherent in the realm
		of e-learning technology. Prioritizing educational value is a nuanced task, requiring a
		delicate balance between user and educational experiences.
	</p>

	<p>
		This demands the creation of intuitive interfaces that guide students toward choices
		that may be more challenging but ultimately more enriching. Tracking users' progress
		over time is a distinctive challenge that necessitates the management of substantial
		data. This, in turn, leads to scaling challenges usually associated with platforms
		experiencing much higher traffic.
	</p>

	<p>
		Moreover, supporting multi-tenancy for different brands adds another layer of
		complexity. Each brand has its distinct visual language and audience needs, requiring a
		system that balances flexibility and standardization, ensuring it responds to diverse
		needs while remaining easy to maintain.
	</p>

	<h2>How We Address These Challenges</h2>

	<div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:-mx-24">
		{
			howWeAddressChallenges.map((item) => (
				<Card>
					<p class="text-xl font-semibold">{item.title}</p>
					<p>{item.description}</p>
				</Card>
			))
		}
	</div>

	<h2>Our stack</h2>
	<div class="grid grid-cols-3 sm:grid-cols-4 md:grid-cols-6">
		{
			stack.map((item) => (
				<div class="flex items-center justify-center">
					<Image
						src={item.src}
						alt={item.alt}
						width="40"
						height="40"
						class="grayscale w-auto"
					/>
				</div>
			))
		}
	</div>

	<h2>Testimonials from our team</h2>
	<div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-3 lg:-mx-24">
		{
			testimonials.map((testimonial) => (
				<Card>
					<p class="text-sm leading-6">{testimonial.text}</p>
					<div class="flex gap-4 items-center">
						<img
							src={testimonial.photo}
							alt={testimonial.name}
							width="50"
							height="50"
							class="rounded-full"
						/>
						<div>
							<p>{testimonial.name}</p>
							<p class="text-sm text-gray-500">{testimonial.role}</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</Card>
			))
		}
	</div>
</ContentPage>
